org.overture.core.tests

Class AbsResultTest<R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.overture.core.tests.AbsResultTest<R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - the (user-provided) type of results this test operates on
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParamFineGrainTest, ParamStandardTest

    public abstract class AbsResultTest<R>
extends Object
    Top level class for new tests framework. Provides common result handling code to all other test classes. This class should not be subclassed directly. Use one of its existing subclasses instead. Test results are always stored with UTF-8 encoding.
    Author:
    ldc
    See Also:
    ParamExamplesTest, ParamExternalsTest, ParamFineGrainTest, ParamStandardTest

      • deSerializeResult

        public R deSerializeResult(String resultPath)
                    throws FileNotFoundException,
                           IOException
        Deserialize test results. This method is capable of deserializing most results, provided the correct type information is provided via getResultType(). If your results are too complex for this method or if you are not using JSON to store then, them you must override the entire method.
        Parameters:
        resultPath - the file path to the stored result file
        Returns:
        the deserialized stored result
        Throws:
        IOException
        FileNotFoundException

      • getResultType

        public abstract Type getResultType()
        Calculate the type of the test result. This method must be overridden to provide the specific result type for each test. When doing so, you can use the snippet below (replacing R with the actual type of your result). Keep in mind this does not work for wildcards or type parameters. You must declare the actual type.
        Type resultType = new TypeToken< R >() {}.getType();
        return resultType;
        Returns:
        the Type of the result file
        See Also:
        TypeToken

      • getUpdatePropertyString

        protected abstract String getUpdatePropertyString()
        Return the Java System property to update this set of tests. Should have the following naming scheme: tests.update.[module].[testId].

        The test ID must be unique to each test class. Module is just there to avoid name clashes so the name of the module is enough.
        Returns:

      • testUpdate

        protected void testUpdate(R actual)
                   throws ParserException,
                          LexException,
                          IOException
        Update the result file for this test. Result serialization is done with JSON and this should adequate for most users. If you need an alternative format, you may override this method.
        Parameters:

        Throws:
        ParserException
        LexException

      • updateCheck

        protected boolean updateCheck()
        Check if test running in result update mode. This is done by consulting the update property as returned by { getUpdatePropertyString().
        Returns:
        true if test is running in update mode. False otherwise

      • compareResults

        public abstract void compareResults(R actual,
                                    R expected)
        Compare output of the processed model with previously stored result. This method must be overridden to implement result comparison behavior. Don't forget to assert something!
        Parameters:
        actual - the processed model
        expected - the stored result
